{
  "stem": "8892.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then he had to slice it up, you know, clean the counter part up where the [INAUDIBLE] meat was.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in the end, when it sort of started to be going on for years, he already resorted, and he accepted the meat with my father, because they all paid for him for that, you know?",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But just-- just a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At one point, my sister was very sick, and a doctor ordered that she must have red meat, must have beef.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father would send the meat over, extra pounds, to the closest neighbor-- the Gentile people-- to cook it up, because heaven help we would cook, you know, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That didn't go that far.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And just to feed my sister, Edith, because she was so anemic.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember that too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this is-- this is when I had-- and then he would always preach-- I wanted, when I was approaching finishing eighth grade, I wanted to go higher education.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I begged and cried, and my father's comment was, not a Jewish girl doesn't need education.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish-- you know-- and for my sister, they give-- but my sister and I have seven-- seven years between us, and seven days, to be exact.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when my time came, the [INAUDIBLE] was already there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they did not concentrate that I should have the schooling, and I was the one who really begged them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So finally, he resigned that, after the eighth grade, I will take courses summertime.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if I-- if I passed, then I could go into a what they called [NON-ENGLISH], which was a third grade of, like-- how they call it?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was like-- was it like high school?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because after eighth grade, I think it would be high school, OK?",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
